f nostalgic memories in discussions of trauma, attending to their interactions in public spaces, patriotic symbolism and rituals, popular culture, cinema, religion, museums, and memorials. The contributors emphasize the role of media and other mass-cultural technologies in disseminating images and narratives related to traumatic and nostalgic experiences. These essays ultimately bring to light the frequently overlooked role of nostalgic longing in shaping the discursive, visual, and material aspects of collective trauma.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCollective memory. 0aMemory. 0aNostalgia. 0aPsychic trauma. 4aContemporary History. 4aContemporary Society. 4aHeritage Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aInterdisciplinary Studies. 4aMedia Studies. 7aHISTORY / Military / Wars & Conflicts (Other).2bisacsh  aNostalgia, Trauma, Memory, Media.1 aArav, Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerg, Mariecke van den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrimell, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHollmann, Joshua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiere, Lucien van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiere, Lucien, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aO'Donohoe, M. Paula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPanico, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeters, Mathijs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSremac, Srdjan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/